newsitem.title: USA: FCOJ futures end at lows, Jan hits contract low.
newsitem.headline: FCOJ futures end at lows, Jan hits contract low.

text.p: NYCE frozen concentrated orange juice futures closed down sharply for the second straight session, pressuring the most-active January contract to a lifetime low and toward key support at 100.00 cents a lb.
Trade selling made up most of the day's activity, estimated at 1,500 lots.
January closed down 1.60 at 101.10, having ranged from 102.70 to 101.05, its contract low. The back months ended 1.30 to 0.95 weaker.
March and May also fell to lifetime lows of 103.25 and 105.50, respectively.
